ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Great class if you can get in
It is a simulation-based class looking at ethical dilemmas that arise for individuals making decisions that effect the public. I would recommend the class.

An experiential, yet deliberate approach to engaging with ethical challenges. Students will gain a greater understanding of their own ethical framework and leave the class with the ability to better analyze, understand, and rationalize their decisions in accordance with their own moral and practical considerations.
